  "text": "O-N 2 O and this statistical technique provides an accurate description of the central tendency of the data. By definition, the standard ellipse contains *40% of the data, is centered on the mean and has standard deviations of the bivariate data as semi-axes (Fig. 2 ) [CITATION_1] 64] . The data and an R file that contains the code to perform the statistical analyses and create the figures shown here are found at https://github.com/jjvenky/Global-N2O-Ellipses. ",
